Parliament has not ratified the amendment for the release of Tymosenko
The Ukrainian parliament refused, in the framework of an amendment to the criminal law, the cancellation of the paragraph on the indictment of Julia Tymosenko, the leader of the opposition.
MEPs refused at second reading the draft amendment to the reduction of the sentences for economic crimes, which could have opened the doors of freedom for the ex-Première Minister currently imprisoned.
tymosenko was sentenced in October to 7 years in prison for an agreement in principle disadvantageous with Russia for the purchase of natural gas.
The judgment is not final and the court must rule on the appeal of the sentenced in December.
tymosenko calls the judgment of revenge policy of the regime and triggered a process of suspicions of bias of the court also to the west.
The project to annul paragraph 365 of the criminal law, on the basis of which the Minister ex-Premère was sentenced, was signed by 147 Members.
It would have required 226 votes to approve it.
