France and the rest of Europe are in the viewfinder of investors.
A tornado of Statistics rose Tuesday on Europe.
Each state has published the information reltives to GDP for the 3 A.
The Czech economy has stagnated this last quarter, while France and Germany are growing.
The bond market from the inquiry.
Investors look not only Italy, but also Spain, France, Austria and others.
The offices of the statistics of the euro area, Germany, Czech Republic and other European countries have published earlier their visions of economic development for the third quarter.
The GDP of Germany has forecast growth of 0.5%, that of France by 0.4%.
The two countries have changed the data for the second quarter in which Germany is better placed than expected (growth of 0.3% instead of the 0.1% expected), but France reported a slight decrease of 0.1% (it was at the origin of stagnation).
The Czech economy was a growth of 1.5% in the third quarter.
But the GDP has stagnated and according to the Office of the Czech Statistical it is confirmed that it is moving towards a progressive decline in economic growth.
The results are worse than the forecast of analysts.
The most important events:
The Budgetary Czech was a growth of 1.5% in the third quarter but has stagnated during the last quarter.
The German economy has been a growth in the third quarter of 0, 5% according to the data and recalculated periodically.
The economy of the euro area and the European Union was a growth of 0.2% between July and September compared with the previous quarter, in line with what analysts had predicted.
The Greek economy has dropped by 5.2%.
The yield on bonds in ten years is 28.45%
Bond yields of Spain and Italy are increasing to critical limits.
The problems begin to feel in Austria, France, Belgium, etc.
