Iranian students are prepared to die for the nuclear program of their country.
They have created a human shield
A few hundred students graduate schools have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
They want to support this gesture by the nuclear program of their country in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
Students began to pray at noon before the site and then called the death of the EU and Israel.
A few hundred students from the universities of Isfahan have created a human shield Tuesday around the nuclear technology centre of Isfahan where is processed uranium.
They have thus stated openly that they will take the nuclear program of their countries, risking their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) found in its last information that Iran has continued to strengthen its nuclear weapons.
Some in Israel of a possible attack Iranian nuclear facilities.
Students began to pray at noon before the site and then called the death of the EU and Israel.
In the case of an attack, the aim would be to destroy Iran's nuclear program, the target would be not only Isfahan, but also the site of Natanz where is enriched uranium.
Feeding a child obese: does not take breakfast and takes to the deli for lunch
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 are overweight, 9% of écoliersont a weight above average and 5% are obese.
As the current research obese children come from families that unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important is the environment in which human beings and the models that surround it.
On the tables of obese children found for example, of the deli 50% more often than in the families of children in normal weight.
19% of obese had french fries at lunch according to the survey conducted with a share of awareness "Obesity is not a chance"
In the families of small large sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most school children today - only 15% replied that at least once a week parents found the time for movement.
Survey conducted on 900 children
The survey was conducted during the last school year and involved 900 primary school children in Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not by chance," action supported by the general health and Unilever.
Since the beginning it is more than 12000 students from sixth to third who enrolled in this project.
One of the factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children are overweight or obese, is the absence of adequate food and not enough exercise.
"Only half the children interviewed indicated, for instance, eat 5 times per day déjeuner-en small cases - lunch - dinner goûter-, which is a basic principles of good food," says one of the results of the investigation.
Without breakfast and lunch at the deli
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have a healthy development it takes a few basic details such as a small lunch in family at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of students "families eat at the same time.
In the majority of families each takes its breakfast alone.
And the worst was identified that a tenth of the population does not at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The survey showed that in the families of obese children are more often French fries unhealthy.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drink each day of sugar-sweetened drinks (70%).
More than 40% of children questioned made sport regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepares you eat
Another part of the investigation has allowed children (204 boys and 172 girls of 13 schools) to prepare its own food from opportunities proposed according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children from 12 to 15 years are far away, in terms of a healthy diet, the ideal."
Among their favourite meals there is a lot of cakes, meat and sweets.
"The more alarming is a strong preference for the sweet lemonades," is indicated in the results of the investigation.
For lunch are the pulp who took place just before the first white meat.
The children were not at all to starch and preference for fish and vegetables was very low.
Focus on health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the time they receive the information.
"During a control of a group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the awareness session" Obesity is not by chance, "was listened to a definite willingness to move towards a healthy diet," indicate the results of the investigation.
The most prominent was for example, with regard to the lemonades sweet because the children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children are most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as a main dish and reduce the flat sweet and "knedliky" (Specialty Czech pellets of bread flour or potatoes).
