How have evolved travel prices since 1989
Until 1989 there were only 5 in Czechoslovakia travel agencies of state: Cedok, Sporturist, elements, Rekrea and Autotourist.
Travel agencies at the time of travel, especially in the countries of the socialist bloc, because travel to the west were very limited.
Czech tourists were traveling for the holidays in East Germany, Soviet Union (Sochi, Crimea and Black Sea), Bulgaria, Romania (the two Black Sea) and Hungary (Balaton).
A large exception for the period from 1962 to 1972 when he was authorized to travel in Yugoslavia and then the regime began to have a fondness for the west and travel to Yugoslavia were very limited for tourists Czech.
The great paradox of the socialist era was that he was not authorized for the citizens of the Socialist block (also for African-American) to travel individually even in the framework of the socialist countries.
In the case where the Czechoslovak citizen wanted to travel individually for example, in Poland and the Soviet Union he needed a letter of invitation if not the individual was not authorized.
Travel agencies at that time also offered travel to the West but had to wait in line all night with a sleeping bag or have a "good standard" within the travel agency.
And even after that this was not yet won.
The agreement for the currency that was the condition for travel to the west was denied to people "politically incorrect" who could not travel at all.
The Czechoslovak currency was not, however, and it was not possible to obtain financial resources without the agreement of foreign currency (Western) to travel to the west.
The Czechs were most often their holidays in the country where there were therefore many country houses and cottages that the Czechs are bought and this usually lasts up to now.
Travel of Czechs have since been since 1989 a major revolution.
Although until 1989 the holidays in East Germany and Bulgaria were maximum, the Czechs have spent the last year abroad 4 million vacation days in countries around the world.
The great paradox which we have not aware today is that the country's most popular is Croatia where it was not possible to go freely until 1989 as part of Yugoslavia at the time.
The abolition of visas in the 90 s of the last century in the neighbouring countries of the west have caused a huge wave of visits of short duration especially in Vienna in Austria and Germany.
The Czechs could not for a long time travel by air to the west that everyone wanted to see at least a moment.
For example, in Paris organizations travel the Czechs were sleeping in tents in parks because our revenues, we were unable to pay the hotel or a pension.
The typical feature of a Czechs was at the time of transfer its own food, sausage, etc... To save.
Another important moment was also the interchangeability of the Czech koruna has allowed our tourists finally after decades of being able to freely buy the currency.
Our standard of living as well as the average salary increased which resulted in around the year 1997 another important moment.
Thanks to a growing demand for travel travel agencies have begun since 1997 to prepare towers with bonds by charter air through contracts have extraordinarily reduced costs compared to what there was before.
In the late 90 s of the last century the Czechs had links without visas with virtually most developed countries around the world to share the EU who later have facilitated our trips.
Another interesting time in the history of tourism post-revolution was prepared, when the first charter air to a country exotic, Thailand, from the Czech Republic.
Since this year as each year of direct air charter take Czech tourists in the distant hot countries; this winter there will be 12 exotic destinations from the Czech Republic.
This is more than 100000 Czechs who visit the country each year exotic!
Still an interesting time in this period that symbolizes our development post-revolution arrived in 2008.
On November 17, 2008, the EU have abolished visas for Czech tourists and allowed our country to join completely in the group of developed countries.
Also in 2008 the Czechs for the first time in history have spent more than half of their holidays abroad (50, 3%) and for the first time in history spent more than $15 000 per person for a vacation abroad including the annexes. Crowns per person.
The General Assembly must find its President but it may end with a situation without solution "a pat"
Nearly 5 months already football Czech President and it is without risk that the successor of Ivan Hasek at the head of the Football Association of the Czech Republic is not yet known even after a General Assembly to be held on Thursday at Nymburk.
However there is still no agreement on how to vote is required.
Without this agreement it is not possible to begin to vote for one of the three candidates.
jindrich Rajchl, Miroslav Pelta and Tomas Paclik are interested in the direction of the Czech football.
Hašek has resigned in June and during his departure called on his colleagues has come together and find a strong personality who will lead the football in the future.
Only during the era after Hašek football came back to differences between the chambers of the Association who may not agree on a joint candidate.
This has fully demonstrated on 16 September when he had to choose a new president.
Delegates to the General Assembly met unnecessarily in the national House in Prague because the negotiation has been blocked and there was not a question of how to elect.
There was no agreement on the fact of who has the right to vote in the General Assembly - only, it seems, the representatives also statutory or officials with full powers.
In this single point there was a partial agreement since that moment with the help also of the Bureau for the state and the right, according to which the representation on the basis of the full power is not possible.
The differences continue always about the regulation for the election.
It is all too clear that the Executive Committee, which in its negotiation planned or extraordinary, has contributed nothing to the situation
Opinions on the possibilitě voting have changed several times but the key point remains the same.
The question is: how to the third round in order not to become the pat.
"The bone of contention is the following fact: either proceed under the Statute or find another model," noted one of three vice-presidents of the Football Association of the Czech Republic Dusan Svoboda that represents professional football in the association.
According to the rules of the model is expected in the third round as the candidates who received the most votes in percentage terms in the Chamber for which he or she is a candidate.
Moravia is prepared according to what is said to withdraw in order that the candidate who receives the highest percentage of votes of the two chambers.
And the Czech Republic is the condition that the winner should have at least two-thirds of the percentages of votes.
"Only this would then lose the idea of two previous rounds and this would completely deny the concept bicameral," admits Svoboda which includes the objections of the Moravian part and that it would be best not to change the regulation and vote under the statutes in force.
It is surprising that Tomas Paclik is also in agreement even if it considers that elections in the Statute benefit the most Pelta among all the candidates.
"I would like to vote according to the statutes of the association."
"For that there is not yet of ideas such as imagined by a representative during the General Assemblies past," said the owner of Victoria Plzen who is a candidate for the first time and which in its submissions is defined primarily against Pelta.
Pelta remains optimistic.
According to him to Nymburk there will be a new President and believes that the candidates will co-operate in the future together and in a constructive way.
"The qualification possible today in Championship should calm down."
"Football will be back on a wave of happiness and there one more drive for a cooperation" adds the officer of Jablonec which of the three has the greatest experience in leading football both professional and at the regional level.
rajchl is more pessimistic.
"I believe in this agreement but unfortunately the situation is very tense."
"This is not a problem between the Czechs and Moravians, but there are trends to change regulations to design."
"This can lead to a blockage at the General Assembly."
"I hope that the healthy reason will prevail," said Rajchl.
There is not much time to a common agreement to all parties.
Some réuunions should take place directly in Montenegro but who can say if any management of football will be complete for the match.
The specially chartered flight in which had to travel to Podgorice between the other Vice-Presidents Dalibor Kucera and Rajchl, has not departed for technical reasons and it was a variant to bring a part of the Executive Committee on the ground of retaliation.
At the end it is the ministerial meeting, which could be held on Wednesday, which should be decisive.
The Minister of Education, Youth and Sports Joseph Dobes would be very pleased to receive the parties torn within the sports association the country and to an agreement.
In the game there is a lot: a state subsidies, the credibility of the football and also the General Assembly of the Union of the Czech Sports that must determine the direction of the sport Czech after the financial problems of Sazka.
