A leap in the blue
Julia Stanek
Paddling pools in optics, pools of UFO beautiful Budapest: Who travel across Europe can live his miracle blue - and after having turned the city or a long promenade- may leave his legs tired in water baths.
A book in which swim basin can experience the most of well-being.
When Iris Meder were traveling research during the past 18 months, there is a subject that should not be missing from his baggage: a bathing suit.
Lying on his back in the water, it was the cupolas artistically arranged, and swam against the marbles Putten who was waiting on the other side of the pool and was to admire the meticulously restored Art Nouveau swimming pools of these converted.
If a covered swimming pool was fun, it noted in his notebook without delay all the details of interest on the type of construction and on the history of the building.
More than 200 swimming pools were surveyed in this way by the architectural historian Meder and she presented in his book already published: "Badefreuden Bain (the joys of everyday life." The municipal swimming pools covered in Munich, the palaces of historical bath in the forest, "buildings of concrete Hardcore" in the Taunus.
It has led its "trips to the bathroom the most exceptional of Central Europe" in 13 countries. In addition to Germany, Austria and Switzerland, she visited places respectively in Italy, France, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Slovenia, Hungary, Romania, Poland and a town in Luxembourg, Serbia and Croatia.
The German 46 years is a real devotee of the culture of the bathtub.
Meder, explained that she has not much interest in the sport but feels particularly attracted to water in a completely different way.
It is irritating that fans of swimming must be content to rest of blue tiles and live with the stench of bleach, whereas the joggers breathe perfume mesmeric of spruce forests, or can listen to the trill of birds in the park.
"I asked myself why a day swimming pools should in fact be always so ugly," said the Viennese.
"I started a collection of beautiful bathroom."
The surface of the water strengthens doubly architecture
A dive in a swimming pool and sauna volatile oils - factor of well-being in swimming are enormous because all the senses are awake, Meder.
And if the builders would have given a little more, the rooms to swim could be a real delight for the eyes: "Instead of a floor has a surface water in the swimming."
"It is a transparent, but reflects on the other hand, however, the beauty of the entire building."
All surfaces are optically a twofold: of vaults high, tiles, art scene.
The volume of image of small format "Badefreuden" is a report of 190 pages on the history of architecture and culture on the oasis of well-being historic - it is certainly to make a leap in the blue.
The collector Meder discovered copies remarkable during his research in Hungary.
In addition to the well-being of beautiful as bathing Széchenyi aged 100 in Budapest, she found water containing nitrate in a natural cave in the bath (karst cave in Miskolc-Tapolca) as well as a spa bath basins filled with water containing the alkali and (in Termálfürdö Városi only) and located in a building in the shape of bottle.
However, the heated outdoor swimming pools of Switzerland and Austria offers spectacular views. As a roof bath of Zurich was the city in its view, can be seen the snow-covered Arlberg route from a pool of St. Anton: The Turkish bath is equipped with a window from which to observe the presentation on the ski area.
Perhaps the design of the more extraordinary awaits the swimmers in one: Aqua Dome Ötztal resembles an UFO landings that has landed on the Alps.
In winter, steam rising from three open shelves, while in the background are the mountains of the Ötztal towards the sky.
The Alhambra in forest black
The smell of bleach is not all pools of the collection Meder.
Many thermal baths are a smell of sulfur, the Árpád-spa in the Bekescsaba Hungarian sends a strong smell of oil, that it is difficult to believe, to be in a health spa.
The smell is alkaline waters therapeutic containing hydrogen carbon that is almost black and its silt you sticks to the skin as soon as you let slip in the pool - a spa experience.
During its quest of the beautiful pools, Iris Meder has also suffered disappointments: When she wanted to visit Bad Luhatschowitz outdoor pool, free and open air of Czechoslovakia, she found herself in a barricaded.
The bath designed by the architèque Dušan Jurkovic in 1902 was now closed.
Looking back through the window of the immeuble-Art New in rouge-blanc-jaune, it noted the vitality of the weeds between the tiles.
It observed an opposite effect in a charming swimming pool in the Black Forest: The Palace of spa of Bad Wildbad.
This building has already survived three phases; we can discover not only elements néo-romains coming out since its creation in 1844 but still a Moorish in Alhambra style that has been added in 1900.
Since its modernization careful of 1995, the thermal bath remains the favorite of the expert in swimming pool, Iris Meder - and not only because it is from Schwarzwald.
"It is already a good performance than to melt building styles were so different in an unit so great," says Meder.
With such a palace, diving in the pool is apparently only a minor issue.
Speculation agricultural
The German bank examines in detail speculation on raw materials
Christian Teevs
The German bank abandonne-elle its commodity speculation?
According to information from SPIEGEL-ONLINE, Josef Ackermann has established a working group to examine the consequences of speculation for the poor of the world.
In January, the leader of the group then wants to draw conclusions from it.
Hamburg -
For the citizens of the Federal Republic, the thing is clear: According to a study, 84% of Germans find it unacceptable that the banks are speculating on raw materials such as corn and wheat.
Two thirds of respondents even require that the German bank and other credit institutions discontinuent this business channel because it increases the problems of the poorest in the world.
It is the result of a decline at the direction of the organization of consumers Foodwatch.
The study is based on a report presented by Foodwatch in mid October.
The author Harald Schumann stressed in this paper that speculation Awards on raw materials, the price goes up and that banks share a complicity to famine.
The campaign consumer protection is specifically against the leader of the Deutsche-Bank, Josef Ackermann, even if the major banks such as Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley are acting in the same way.
Speculation on raw materials was originally introduced to protect against price fluctuations.
But the majority of experts now share the view that the betting public have posted offers and requests - and benefit at the expense of the very poor.
Ackermann was responding to the criticism differently from U.S. competitors: It promised to investigate the allegations and said, "no matter is worth the good reputation of Deutsche Bank."
According to information SPIEGEL ONLINE of an international working group is currently reviewing the accusations of Foodwatch-Report.
The review should be completed by the end of the year, then the results of the Board of Directors of the Deutsche Bank must be submitted - with recommendation, usual.
In late January, the head of the Bank will indicate the consequences to be drawn.
It could result in a reduction in the market of raw materials, or even a complete abandonment.
Ackermann built its Image
The head of Foodwatch Thilo Bode welcomed the news, but at the same time confirmed its criticism of the financial sector: "The speculation on the rise in food prices shows a draconian manner, how banks today to the general interest."
Ackermann is the first banking lobby to be particularly today under obligation.
"The Deutsche Bank must remove all investments in his portfolio, for which the money was invested in speculation," said Bode.
"It is not important, for Mr Ackermann, but it is a question of people hungry or if the reputation of the Deutsche Bank is at stake."
The awareness of Ackermann may seem at first sight surprising, but it is clear that the CEO of the group wants to present a perfect image, a few months before he leaves office.
Deutsche Bank did announce on Monday that the president of the Administrative Council will not change what is provided for in the Administrative Council.
Ll could improve its brand image with the abandonment of agricultural speculation controversial.
And about potential losses, it has little to worry about - his successor will therefore deal with these.
One in two would terminate investments on raw materials.
Foodwatch strives to maintain strong pressure on the Manager.
To date more than 30 000 Internet users have already participated in the campaign of the organization.
Bode published the survey Tuesday, November 7 and 8 cent decline the Institute conducted questionnaires from 1001 people.
Just eleven percent have found it legitimate that Deutsche Bank proposes investments for which bets on prices of food products are made.
Many clients of the bank would also personal consequences if they knew that their bank is involved in such operations: one on two would terminate, following the survey, all investments for which money is injected into the speculation on raw materials.
43 percent déconseilleraient of such a bank to their environment, 49% said they would at the termination of their account to change d "bank.
21th home in Vienna
The Pavilion who moved
By Ingeborg Wiensowski
A history of architecture with senior, low and a Happy End: the Austrian flag for exhibitions in Brussels in 1958 won awards, was a museum in Vienna, remained empty and then fell in ruins.
Now it is open to new and takes place of house of exposure.
If there is an enthusiasm for post-war modern architecture, for his clear forms, its hangars glass, its patterns and bold and its new construction materials that are typical of the belief to technical progress, then the flag of the Austrian architect Karl schwanzer for the event in Brussels in 1958 is a good and famous example.
The Pavilion Schwanzer was formerly the "Grand Prix for Architecture" for its construction steel and glass, and suspended.
The construction is up to our days as an important step in contemporary architecture.
He has made the architects if famous, he has also built the Pavilion for the Austrian.
With its legendary home to four cylinders BMW and its adjacent construction in Munich, it finally became famous at the international level in 1973.
His draft flag as a temporary construction had been exposed after the world in the Garden Switzerland at the station in the south of Vienna, has been transformed, and in 1962 a museum of the 20th century opened -
But the building was not physically or technically adapted for a museum - no walls to the works of art, not a good environment.
However it was also long used, until contemporary art receives a new building in Vienna.
Since 2001 the building was empty and has become increasingly dilapidated.
Now the architect Adolf Krischanitz has transformed the Pavilion, it is now known as "House of the 21th century" and will in future be used as a museum for contemporary art.
On Tuesday evening the Belvedere museum opened, which owns the house, the first exhibition - a stroke of luck at any point of view.
The new start has been carried out by Agnès Husslein-Arco, which has become the new Director in 2007 of the gallery Austrian Belvedere.
Husslein-Arco, has promoted an art historian at a considerable career in his youth, figure skater, subsequently in Sotheby's, at the Guggenheim Museum and as a founding director of the Museum of Modern Art in Salzburg, it has led to the transformation work with politicians and the protection of monuments, she obtained of public funds and private sponsorship and exploitation.
Except contemporary art, the works of sculptor Fritz Wotruba which the foundation of the same name have been exposed, a café and bookstore, and an office must be built.
Strict monitoring, small budget
For the Krischanitz was the ideal interpreter.
Not only because it had transformed and expanded with sensitivity the secession of Joseph Olbracht and that he had won the competition, but because he had studied at the Technical University of Vienna, and for him the flag was "an extremely important" place where he had seen "virtually every weekend" exhibits.
He knew the original project, and he knew the problems of the building, who lost in generosity and lightness following his visit to Vienna and by its change of use.
In the current changes, there were major problems: the building was "a chasm energy," said Krischanitz.
The profiles of windows of glass facades were changed insulation, glass fibre reinforced glass and the roof was replaced by a glass of safety.
The beams of thermal bridges have been strengthened or replaced, and coatings filled with asbestos have been rehabilitated.
Two basements made room for the new operation, a sign of light, between the house and the road provides lighting, a bridge leads to the entry - it is almost a new construction, but always the slight Schwanzer Pavilion.
The exterior doors origins remained, the house is painted in a hue protection against rust colour red-brown.
And the movie theatre is even exactly identical to what it once was.
And all this under close supervision of the competent authorities for monuments and with a small budget.
"Often materials that are good and cheap were to be found, and that appeal also to the Office of the protection monuments," says Krischanitz and it draws attention to a soil crude underground.
Despite all the constraints, the problems and the transformations, the building remained flexible and light.
This would have been difficult with the Pavilion, "which came from Brussels," said Krischanitz recently, a story typical of "Drop-in-the-City."
Such an architecture is "always in the wrong place" and still wants to "awaken the conscience."
But in this case the House of the 21th century is not in the wrong place, because if it is a stroke of luck: urban construction around the Garden Switzerland is precisely the "neighbourhood of the Central Station" any newly planned, with offices and apartments.
And another stroke of luck may occur: the House of the 21th century could benefit from the support of another construction Krischanitz, because the collector Francesca von Habsburg purchased the art centre temporary Berlin, and as he said, it is already negotiating with the city in order to obtain a site in the vicinity of the Garden Switzerland.
Bahn plans a crisis winter in the millions.
The railway company has developed a plan-crise, which aims to prevent accidents train in winter.
The number of employees should double.
It costs millions.
In the fight against the rail accidents related to the winter season and delays, the railway company Deutsche Bahn "in this regard will spend more than 70 million this year.
The newspaper "Bild" -Zeitung reported in advance on a plan-crise internal to the group, that investments of a total of approximately EUR 300 million would be set up in 2015.
This should allow greater availability of vehicles and the rail network also in the case of extreme weather.
The number of employees internal and external for snow removal of rail facilities and docks should between other double and go to 16.000 people.
The goal is to rid the docks of snow and ice until the beginning of the phase of service and 90 percent of the needed to service within four to five hours.
Two months ago the Chief of Station Rüdiger Grube warned the government and industry at a conference at the top of the train accidents occurred also this winter.
Last winter the railway company has had a great many problems for the transport of "users, because it lacks between other reserves in case of inclement weather conditions.
That is how many new regional trains have been waiting for years for an authority on the part of the Department of the railways.
In addition, there is a delay in the delivery of ICE trains.
The railway company has since years of what to do, as it must have the axles of trains ICE significantly more often in the workshop, after a break of axles took place on an ICE in the Central Station in Cologne.
The German bank Deutsche Bank "pays millions of penalties in the US.
After the case of the chief Josef Ackermann there is something new in the US: the German bank Deutsche Bank "must pay a fine" of two million.
As if the problems of the Deutsche Bank were not already sufficient, the past of this giant sector caught up in the US: the Institute of Frankfurt pay in comparison to $145 million (EUR 106 million) to settle a dispute because of the bankruptcy of five large cooperative banks during the financial crisis.
It is the sale of mortgage documents.
The regulator of financial markets NCUA door to major banks a series of charges, and to have this encourage cooperative banks to make false claims about the purchase of financial products; they would have minimized the risks.
These documents have lost considerable value during the financial crisis and have led to banks to the bottom.
"We are satisfied, to have been able to find a solution to this issue, without the parties initiate a procedure to the court," said an interlocutor of Deutsche Bank in New York.
The Bank has recognized in comparison no fault.
This also applies to the Citigroup, which is committed to a payment of $20.5 million.
The President of NCUA Debbie Matz welcomed the concessions of the two banks.
The National Credit Union Administration (NCUA) responsible for cooperative banks of USA and intervenes in case of bankruptcy, in order to protect the deposits of clients.
The NCUA tries to repair the damage incurred billions of dollars.
The comparisons made now are the first of their kind.
The regulator has also taken other large banks to party and it has been brought before the Court JP Morgan Chase, the Royal Bank of Scotland and Goldman Sachs.
With regard to the issue of mortgage documents it is of "Mortgage-backed Securities."
Credit companies are at the base.
When the U.S. housing bubble burst in 2007, This has been fatal to a large number of companies.
In September 2008, at the top of the financial crisis, the U.S. investment bank Lehman Brothers collapsed.
Even if the events are already a few years ago, at the present time it blows on the banks of a wind storm.
Investors and supervisory authorities have brought many remedies for redress and to punish breaches.
The Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA) triggered the biggest wave of complaints.
It accuses 18 major international banks, the two financial real estate d "state U.S. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac" benefit in kind during business Mortgage of approximately $200 billion.
Deutsche Bank must also file an appeal with the FHFA, this is of several transactions for a total amount of $14.2 billion for the years 2005 to 2007.
The supervisory authorities, that the Frankfurter meets "substantial losses" but without a specific amount.
Deutsche Bank had dismissed the claims as unjustified and vows to defend themselves.
