The bank scandal of Lake of Zurich
The Bank the most adventurous of Europe is not in France or Italy, but in Switzerland.
UBS has been almost in bankruptcy the financial crisis and patina meanwhile from one crisis to another.
It is a German who must lead now.
This is certainly not what Axel Weber's "was imagined.
After his departure of the head of the Bundesbank; it has been informed in July that it would occupy a position in 2013 almost as spectacular: Chairman of the Board of Directors of the great Swiss bank UBS - a major step towards a career unexpected and lucrative.
Axel Weber has publicly welcomed, has welcomed Switzerland; for its beauty and the UBS for its strength and has recently obtained from kind comments on the future colleagues.
"The UBS has passed the Turnaround."
"I look forward to working with Kaspar Villiger and Oswald Grübel."
And yet, as early as September it was clear that everything was going to change.
A merchant of securities of UBS in London had diverted all the safety systems of the Bank and had singed approximately EUR 1.7 billion.
The head of the Board of Directors of the UBS Grübel Oswald, a banker known not only in Switzerland, has had to leave.
The Chairman of the Board of Directors of the UBS is regarded as since suffering - and all are asking: When Axel Weber does finally?
We have already learned that Weber can be advised of the bank from February 2012.
And it will resume the presidency of administration already in May - not in 2013, as communicated the bank on Tuesday.
For Axel Weber it becomes difficult.
It is not much more banker, "economy professor and President of the bank, and certainly would have needed a period of adjustment.
At one time it assumed responsibility for the strategy of a bank, which has yet to prove once again that it has long since earned the title of "the largest bank to scandal in Europe."
Indeed, the UBS was a huge - until recently, it was the largest asset manager in the world, and on the other, it patina for years of a scandal to another.
Nothing, it seems, are the proud if Swiss bank.
It started during the financial crisis.
Until 2007 the UBS had an excellent reputation.
The image of the Swiss asset manager, silent and sound, but also shrewd, she combined with ambitious objectives: it also wanted to become, in the field of investment banking, a very large bank.
Therefore the UBS managed on one side in 2007 with $1.6 billion more money from a wealthy clientele than any other bank in the world.
On the other hand, it had raised as an investment bank in the league of the largest banks in the world.
This has made an impression.
The former banker Hans Geiger and later Professor of bank for many years in Zurich said: "I have always taken the UBS as a model of good bank to my students."
"In the current perspective, we wonder: how is it that I could have simply mistaken to this point?"
It is profoundly wrong.
In 2007 it emerged that for the first time something was amiss at UBS.
In the middle of the year the President Peter Wuffli withdrew from surprisingly, which was previously regarded as a high intellectual and a brilliant banker.
A few months later it was why it was gone.
The division of the bank had singed with documents and has risen to write off billions.
To support this, the UBS announced a capital increase in the amount of 13 billion francs and made a cross.
For this she did find investors, but that, shortly before, would have her: a bottom of Asian state non-transparent from Singapore and an Arab state, which was passed over in silence, to the point where it has never even learned his name.
"This was the first time.
In April 2008 it has worsened.
The bank was to announce losses amounting to billions, the Chairman of the Board of Directors Ospel Marcel, who in 2006 was still the second Board of Directors paid to Switzerland, withdrew.
In October 2008 the disaster followed: the UBS was, given its mistakes, investment in the financial crisis before the bankruptcy and had to be rescued by the state.
The National Bank has bought from UBS tens of billions of securities issues, the Swiss Confederation has given six billion francs for bonds convertible into shares, for which she could become co-owner of the bank.
Any Switzerland was hit - because it noted how this can be dramatic for a small country, to house if large banks.
Finally, the balance sheet total of the 2007 s "UBS rose to more than five times the economic performance of Switzerland (see chart).
"We have not been able to save the UBS once again," says the researcher of banks, Geiger.
After the first disaster as a result of the second.
Already a few months before, the UBS had capitulated due to a tax dispute with America and was ready to publish the data from the wealthy clientele, who had defrauded the taxman perhaps with the help of the Bank.
In addition, she accepted a payment of $780 million - for repayment of unjustified profits from these transactions with a fine.
And UBS has more or less published that she had assisted in tax fraud.
At the same time she lost something that has always been its capital in competition with the rich clients: the prestige of the discretion.
After the scandal Swiss bank secrecy has not been the same.
It was followed by the withdrawal of the leader of the Board of Directors and the Chair of the Board of Directors.
And the exodus of money from customers.
And the bank had lost its credibility in a few months in the two main business sectors: investment banking because of poor speculation and asset management because of the assistance to tax fraud.
And, as there was a little calm, and as previously thought, that UBS would perform this was followed by this unfortunate history of title: a single merchant as rocketing EUR 1.7 billion, before the bank to the realization that something was amiss.
And it publishes: with risk management in investment bank this still does not work.
"With the case Adoboli, it was noted that the control of risks to too little changed," says Martin Janssen, an economist and professor of finance at the University of Zurich.
Also the Chief Financial Officer of a large German bank is safe: "the problem of the UBS is that it was not the control of risks in hand."
However it was exactly the idea of caution, with which Swiss bankers had long since taken their function, that of becoming guardian of the great fortune of the world: not too many risks, but security for the money - and the world could well collapse beyond the Alpine republic.
The treasures of Swiss banks had become the symbol of an unshakeable reliability as Lindt & Sprüngli chocolate are for a particularly noble.
The UBS in Zurich goes hand in hand with the sound of the Swiss private bank - it is only a little more.
Already the situation is.
The Bank has its headquarters in the city of Zurich, which led directly to the Central Station to Lake Zurich, which itself is surrounded by the snowy peaks of Swiss mountains.
The buildings are here prestigious, rents of stores are among the highest in Europe.
As the jewellers Tiffany's are here between stores to Swiss traditions like those of the confectionery Sprüngli.
For centuries Swiss bankers have resided here: the national bank through the palace of the Credit Suisse, private banks Julius Bär as elitist.
It is in the lobby of the UBS by a heavy door.
Inside, the walls are lined with marble, before are thick leather chairs, and next to the logo of the bank, a major label to "safe."
The UBS knows what the client research here: security.
This idea of the Swiss bank has one day or another ruled out of the market - or betrayed the two major Swiss banks, UBS and Credit Suisse, as the head of a small Swiss private bank.
He would prefer not to read his name in the paper, finally as all Swiss bankers it does business with the two large banks.
The UBS would have become far too large, trouve-t" it - particularly in investment banking, where the Anglo-Saxons were also common.
The Swiss have nothing more to say.
"And even so, they have long been adapted to the customs of the Anglo-Saxons."
This was indeed the investment bank that has changed the Anglo-Saxon UBS, it has made high profits and then the debacle: no European financial institution has lost so much money in the jungle of risen as the great Swiss bank.
The disaster became apparent on 15 October 2008.
"This Wednesday, the coalition government of the small countries to seven million people has undertaken the largest rescue operation in the history of their nation," writes the author Lukas Hässig in his book "The crash of the UBS."
With up to 68 billion francs, or approximately EUR 45 billion, the politicians have agreed to save from bankruptcy the vast bank.
How could this happen?
If we speak with Swiss bankers, they see the problem, especially to the size of the UBS.
In June 1998 two of the three major Swiss banks have entered into a huge group.
A bank was created, which was already too big for the small Switzerland - and has been steadily increasing.
On the whole, it is that the two banks prédécesseuses different of the UBS have completed: a bank rich, but lethargy with as strong point asset management in Zurich and a poor, but certainly more already highly internationalised.
Suddenly, the international investment banks have had access to a lot of money, with which they have been able to turn a huge wheel.
Two names are associated with the rise of UBS: Peter Wuffli, from 2001 to 2007 Head of UBS group, and Marcel Ospel, formerly Chairman of the Board.
"I have always thought that Wuffli and Ospel constituted a dream team," says the researcher of banks, Hans Geiger.
"Wuffli, the great intellectual modest, which are very well in models and statistics, and Ospel, the intuitive, which made its way to the top with the learning of the bank."
But Ospel has relied until the end to Wuffli.
And wuffli would probably have committed at the end a fatal flaw: "It was thought that its models were the reality," says Geiger.
"This is a tragic fall."
Tragic, perhaps.
One thing is clear: the exuberance arrived before the fall.
The staff of the UBS remembers clearly meetings of leaders in which the leader of the group Wuffli always gave the same watchword: a Goldman Sachs.
The bank was the U.S. investment bank the most powerful in the world.
It commissioned the "League Tables" the rankings, which have documented at that time the success of the banks.
After all UBS wanted to go up at the top.
Some steps have already been successful.
In case of currencies and transactions of securities it has played a very important role.
The business advisors, who had the responsibility, stressed however a weakness: in the international operations of interest, in the jargon banking "Fixed Income," there would be a huge difference compared with larger banks.
The UBS would have gaps in products of mortgages.
To fill this gap, UBS has launched into an adventure, which nearly cost him his life.
Hungry for growth, it is the bank itself that a fund management created before it in the U.S. sub-prime investments that have invested.
It has been a machine massive who packaged and documents of value based on U.S. mortgages - but which has also retained.
Even when other banks were looking for a long time to get down.
"Yet in the summer of 2007, while the U.S. housing market was in flames, the UBS purchased here," said Geiger, the banking expert.
More euphoria is more the fall is brutal.
A manager after another had to leave, when put an end to the attempts proved to be more difficult than was thought.
Positions with UBS became ejection and are so far bancaux.
The bank has an almost impossible task.
It must find a strategy for a bank, for which all business models suggested have disappeared.
The researcher bank, Geiger has already an idea: put an end to the investment bank, concentration in the management of assets, return to roots.
But the bank does not (yet) go that far.
But the investment bank must atrophying vigorously, as far as this is clear so far.
Next Thursday the Head of Sergio Ermotti bank wants to present the world its future strategy.
The Italo-suisse 51 years of age was only supposed to be transitional when the bank broke away with surprise of his predecessor Grübel.
Meanwhile, it emerged: it must lead to the business of UBS, announced Tuesday, the Bank of Zurich.
Ermotti wants to reduce the investment bank to the status of the mid-1990 s.
It cancels 3500 jobs.
But it will not be enough.
The UBS needs a vision.
Which is it?
What does it want to earn money?
These are the questions that Axel Weber has certainly already asked.
He said publicly until now only that he would seek an apartment with his wife in Zurich.
The next year.
