Crows smart spread in cities
In many places, rooks are considered "problem birds" But experts say that these highly intelligent animals are no longer hunt cities for a long time.
Some like them, others want to get rid of them as quickly as possible. The crows belong to the city for centuries, but in many communities residents "complaints due to the dirt and noise of animals.
An antidote against the "° problem of birds" is not yet in sight.
In the first ostfriesisch symposium on crows, experts have said that this is no longer possible to hunt the rooks cities.
Experts from all over Germany deliberated on the possible solutions.
They are looking for alternatives in cities
The protectors of the nature of the cities based also on the exodus of the especially protected: The use of chemicals in agriculture destroy more and more officers.
Hunting, development and tree breeding typical made life difficult to birds.
Crows are under the protection of nature.
There are large colonies with more than 600 pairs of breeding in the westfälischen Soest, in the northwest including Jever, taken and Achim near Bremen and in Leer.
In 2005, a controversial project had earned negative ads because of the massacre of crows in this region.
Critics have found the capture of birds in traps and their killing with clubs particularly brutal.
"The normal expulsion, the exclusion, is pointless," found the planner of the city and the landscape of Leer, Werner Klöver.
The destruction of nests with the help of water pressure or trees, often produces unintended consequences, "said the expert Manfred Kaiser environment to Lahr in Baden-Württemberg.
"The animals away, the large colonies divide and they disperse in other places."
L "displacement is conceivable only in exceptional cases such as hospitals, retirement homes or schools.
"We are forced to live with them, we can no longer exterminate them."
The problem does not resolve in cities without the inclusion of the periphery, according to the opinion of the mayor Wolfgang Kellner of Leer.
Conceivable is a combination of the ousting of animals to an aversif packaging and offers, so as to enable them to relocate.
Psychologist and ethnologist, Uta Maria Jürgens tried "signs info in place of chainsaws" to establish relations with the completely different: "We can finally better support a button in the face with a dose of self-confidence."
Jürgens has co-founded the Ascheberger-cheminement-éducatif baskets in Schleswig-Holstein, highway signs advising on the lives of these, very intelligent.
This project has been in the meantime adopted by tourists.
Jürgen gave his own opinion about the critical of the noise caused by birds: "this is a large number of communication, these oiseaux-là have much to say."
The intelligence and the ability of animals are legendary: The rooks do not use only work instruments to arrive at a special treat but they manufacture their own tools as instruments of work.
The threat of the University of Cambridge tested four rooks recently, how is the intelligence of the birds.
In one experiment, the birds quickly learned that they had to make a scaffold collapse with stones in order to achieve a larva.
Without a lot of training, they recognized that a déterminément stone had to have some size and shape to collapse the platform.
In a second test, crows astute then had to solve a problem more muscular neck.
In a vertically placed cylinder, researchers had placed a small bucket with a larva.
The birds could not reach their spoils with their bills.
However, the researchers had set pieces of wire at their disposal.
All four animals formed a hook with which they fished the small bucket of the small pipe.
Three of the four rooks even from the beginning.
