The event was last Thursday, when the nine judges are gathered for a conference to discuss the petitions for review.
One of the cases in question concerned a lawsuit filed by 26 states challenging the health care reform ambitious passed by Congress last year, a law that has been a rallying point for conservative activists at the national level.
The judges agreed to hear the complaint, in effect, a monumental argument from 5 is expected in March, and the result will probably be conducive to the destabilisation of the presidential race of 2012, which will be growing at the time the court's decision will be made.
