The Court valid "the analog" in Mexico in 2015
The substitution of analog cited by the Examiner is one of the most important changes that the world has suffered the last years
The Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) dismissed the constitutional controversy that the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies made against the presidential decree that the so-called "analog cutoff" from 2021 to 2015, because the eight votes needed to invalidate the have not been met.
A minority of four ministers, including the President of the Court, Juan Silva Meza, considered that President Felipe Calderón has not exceeded its powers when he issued Order in Council which details the actions to be taken to make the transition to digital television.
With this outcome, the constitutional controversy promoted by the Senate of the Republic, was dismissed for not meeting the qualified majority of eight votes for the Court to rule on the constitutionality of the order, or non-constitutionalité and this continues to be in force.
The draft, prepared by the Minister Olga Sánchez Cordero, proposed the declaration of the decree as non-constitutionnel, because of the fact that the regulation of radio and television is a power reserved by law to the Federal Commission of Telecommunications (Cofetel), in contravention of the principles of hierarchical subordination and reserve.
In favour of the project voted only Zaldívar, Mario Jorge Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies have promoted two controversial constitutional to challenge the order and assuming the complaints, the Minister Sánchez Cordero has suspended the application of the Order and of all the actions provided for in the programme for the digital transition.
The plenary session of Ministers resolved also dismiss the complaint made by the Chamber of Deputies, without discussing the project that the Minister Sánchez Cordero is also responsible.
In his speech, the Minister said that he did not agree with the arguments of the project, in the sense that the federal structure may not through general standards for the measures that the government is preparing to.
"I believe that if he did it would affect the autonomy of the regulator," and he recalled that the planning of public policies in strategic areas such as the telecommunications sector is the responsibility of the federal executive, which has the constitutional mandate the direction of the state.
The substitution of the analog by digital reported is one of the most important changes that the world has suffered in recent years and this is reflected in the better exploitation of the radio spectrum, a better quality of the signal and more channels.
The change, has soutenu-t-il, would adjourn the benefits of the decision, which involves a public interest that has not only a technical dimension, "because it also includes economic, social, political and national security."
These issues, has souligné-t-il, "require the operation of a whole system establishes, in accordance with the principle of economic direction of the state, includes a group of powers that the Constitution grants the faculty of the Executive of the state."
He recalled that a large number of countries across the world have already finished the digital transition and they did it through the Executive, despite the fact that they had the very specialized technical bodies.
One cannot conclude that the Commission, in issuing the decree challenged, has invaded a form the sphere of competence of the Congress, because it provides in the administrative sphere compliance with laws issued by the Legislative, assura-t-il.
The analysis of the possibility of a "vote by vote" in Michoacán
According to data provided by PERs, the difference between the first and second place for the election of the Governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 mile 74 minutes total.
The possibility of the count "vote by vote" is a reality in relation to the electoral trial this year in Michoacán, where according to data provided by the Program Électoraux Preliminary Results (PERs) the difference between the first and second place for the election of the Governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 of the 6 mile 74 minutes total.
In this sense, the President of the General Council of the Institute of Michoacán Electoral Institute (AEI), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, the past 9 November, the electoral body has approved a series of guidelines to harmonize local standards to reform federal in electoral matters.
It is recalled that Michoacán has not licensed or its Constitution Policy or its Code Electoral Institute of State or its Electoral Act of Justice, at the same time as the Congress of the State has approved reforms to end shortly before the legal time limit for this trial electoral can enter into force and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel failed its publication in the time limits set by the Act of the Official Journal of the State, with the argument that he had a few objections.
The same 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) has solved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local Legislative Authority and described as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the representative of the state for constitutional reform, because it does not have the right to "punish or challenge."
Interviewed on the possibility of the "vote by vote," María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the guidelines by the Council General of EMI it will be possible to achieve the partial and total votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial count of votes, of one or several packages election, it may be that: the results of the minutes do; there is no record of voting and counting in the file of the ballot box is not in the president of that company; or there are any errors or obvious alterations of minutes.
In addition, the total amount of votes received in all polls of the election will be achieved when there is an indication of the fact that the difference between the assumed candidate winner of the election and the one that took second place in the election is equal to or from below by one percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session is a petition by the representative of the party and / or coalition who made the second of candidates reported.
The total amount of voting can also be achieved if at the end of the count, it is clear that the difference between the assumed candidate winner and the second is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is express the petition of the representative of the political party whose candidate came second, in which case it will exclude the electoral packages that have been subject of the count.
It should be noted that this is the situation of the election of Morelia where, according to the PERs, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 minutes total.
