The new Italian government will be formed on Wednesday
The Prime Minister designated, Mario Monti, will meet tomorrow with the President of Italy to present the new government will face a crisis that has put this country on the brink of economic disaster
The Prime Minister designated, Mario Monti, will meet Wednesday with President of Italy to present the new government will face a crisis that has put Italy on the brink of economic disaster and put at risk all the Eurozone.
A news release of the presidential palace announced that Monti, appointed on Sunday, would meet Wednesday with President, Giorgio Napolitano, to confirm that it can form the Government.
It is expected that it presents a cabinet composed in its majority by technocrats, even if it is not clear when the new executive will assume his position.
Monti said that it would submit its report the result of his conversations with the political parties in his essay to form a government.
"I want to confirm my absolute confidence in our country's ability to overcome this difficult phase," said the former European Commissioner to journalists.
Monti has not said explicitly that he could form a government, but the tone of his comments indicated that the obstacles have been overcome.
"The framework is now well established," he added.
Monti has completed the process to form a government in less than three days, in a reduced time more than usual, while Italy combat a political and financial crisis which pushed the cost of its debt to levels impossible to support.
The new administration headed by former European Commissioner Monti must approve a tough austerity package required by European leaders to recover the confidence in Italy who had been affected.
Noting the pressure on Monti to dispatch, the instability of markets to put the performance of obligations Italian BTP to over 10 years of 7 percent, the level at which Greece and Ireland have duu be saved.
Emma Marcegaglia, leader of the Labour Italian Confindustria, told media after his meeting with Monti: "We said that we would support the government."
We believe that this Government is the last opportunity for Italy to this kind of emergency situation.
The chances of success of Monti have been driven significantly by the support of the PDL party of Silvio Berlusconi, in which the crisis has forced to resign on Saturday.
"We believe that the efforts of the Professor Monti will have a good result," said to the press Angelino Alfano, secretary of the centre-right.
The support of PDL party, the Italian, is the most significant because until now many of its members had been opposed to the Government of that majority technocrat Monti.
Parliamentary support
The new government of Monti must have a strong parliamentary support to implement what probably will be reforms unpopular austerity.
Any blockage or delay in its efforts could cause a new and devastating attack of financial markets.
The Italian association of foreign has added to the pressure by observing that a bankruptcy of Monti would be a disaster.
Monti began Monday its consultations with political parties, trade unions and employer groups and organizations juveniles and women.
It will complete its tour of meetings Tuesday night.
Monti was appointed by Napolitano Sunday, which has empowered an extremely rapid transition in response to the crisis.
After a brief respite at the end of last week, when it was clear that Berlusconi would resign, the costs of Italian debt are now at critical levels between the uncertainty on the success of the new prime minister.
Save Italy, with a public debt of 1.9 trillion euros, it would be too much for the current financial defences of Eurozone.
Monti said that his Government should persist up to future elections, scheduled for 2013, despite widespread predictions on the fact that politicians will provide only the time to implement the reforms before the elections.
Monti said he would like to include politicians in his cabinet, but the major parties insist that it must be made only by specialists, an index of their objections before a process required by the financial pressure.
Political sources reported that the mutual suspicions and disagreements between the parties complicate the trial to include political figures.
