Quinteto included the country in turn to celebrate two decades of trajectory
"" To go to Costa Rica is a dream that became reality "
In the exclusive interview with Viva, bassist Jeff Ament of Pearl Jam, said that the group is prepared to provide one of the best concerts the next Sunday on the National Stadium.
They waited more than 20 years, but the group ensures that for them it will also be a dream come true to occur in this country.
Is that the bassist and founding member Jeff Ament assured, speaking exclusively with Viva, Brazil, last week.
The group is in the wing of its South American tour of celebration of two decades of work and Sunday 20 will make its single stopover in Central America.
That day will come on the National Stadium, from 19:30 hours, the group of Los Angeles The X and nationals of Las Robertas.
This is an excerpt of the conversation, which can be found in La Nación on the Internet.
For its proponents, the fact that Costa Rican Pearl Jam will occur at Costa Rica is a dream come true. Are you aware of what your fans live?
Go to Costa Rica is a dream that has become a reality for us.
This is the second time in South America and Central and so far this has been.
I spent to Costa Rica only once the holidays; it is a country so beautiful and I think we can spend a few days.
We therefore émotionne to bring our music there.
I ask you, because there is a kind of devotion to the group, the fans live with intensity the previous days.
What is your message for your most devoted followers?
Thank you to stay next to us for all these years.
It has taken 21 years to ensure that we achieve Costa Rica; thank you to wait until we regret the fact that so much time had to spend up to this together.
A few people are already saying that his concert is the largest show of the year.
Does this adds a bit of pressure to your visit.
Some of the greatest shows that we have provided over the last 21 years have taken place in the last two weeks.
We have offered a two huge shows in Sao Paolo and we hope that this put us in shape for this concert in Costa Rica.
We are really very keen to produce.
We love this country, we like to do in the surf and the jungle; for the two things, Costa Rica is one of the best countries in the world.
How did you discover Costa Rica and its waves for surfing?
We have many friends and I have a very good friend who lives in Tamarindo and waves are amazing there.
My friends would always to surf in Costa Rica and Nicaragua, to Mexico, are great places to make the surf; that is how we learned, through the UW who like surfing.
Seeing the tour, you with offered shows enormous, with many songs.
What do you have planned for your presentation to Costa Rica?
As we have never products there, we have no restrictions on what we can do.
We will try to make the best show possible, with a wide variety of songs; we will try to interpret two songs from each album and give our fans a good and diverse.
You never repeat the directory.
What is this?
I believe that this is partly because we have nine and we can interpret more than 120 songs and love songs each different, that is why it is very difficult to choose which songs interpret each evening.
When we have two or three songs in the directory that we have more interpreted for a very long time, it helps us to stay focused and surprises us because it reminds us the reasons why we loved these songs and that we can have forgotten.
This fact that the show is more interesting for us and therefore I think it is also becoming more interesting for people.
With this tour, you celebrate 20 years of trajectory.
With hindsight, it is difficult to believe everything that you have been successful?
Yes, absolutely.
First, I believe that none of us had imagined that we would form a large rock group, and the fact that we have done for over 20 years that this is a dream.
We continue to tell our blessings and the fact that we can continue to make music together we émotionne much.
We love and we love to create music.
We are lucky to go places in the world that we have always wanted to go.
Things could get better for us.
That means to you having been a fundamental element in the creation of the grunge?
This has always been a honour for us to form part of this group of major groups.
We are very friends with the people of Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains.
It is surprising when a movement arises from a group of friends and is unusual.
From time to time, a group emerging from a city, but it is much more strange when five or ten groups out at the same time in the same city.
We are proud and it is a honour for us to form part of the group of Seattle.
Yet we play with some of them from time to time.
Last year we participated in a festival with Alice in Chains and we have been in Canada with Mudhoney, we have seen Soundgarden in their tour, therefore we are lucky to still be friends with them all and it is a honour for us to form part of the sound of Seattle that arises.
It is also very strange that a group like the your community united and with the same members for so long.
Yes, four of us have been together for 21 years and Matt (Cameron) joined us 13 years ago, and only this is much more time than many groups normally last.
First, I believe that we are all lucky to be alive and, second, we are all concerned for others.
We are all close friends, and through this there are boulevards musical that give to each of the freedom to experiment.
We have confidence in each other with the music of everyone and this could go better.
Your relationship with the word celebrity has not been easy; however, thanks to your success, you have been able to do what you want.
How do you find a balance?
As we grew up, it was easier for us to find a balance.
We ensure that we do not spend too much time on tour because it is easy to fall into this game of great multitudes and people who like your music.
If we do not forget that people are there to music, it helps us to remember that we must respect the music and what has made, without getting in mind the fact that it is famous and a rock star, which is not really of any one of us.
How do you remember your other project, Mother Love Bone?
I think that we have written to good songs and early this was.
We were a group for almost three years and we have not published a disk before the death of Andy (Andrew Woods).
There has been a lot of frustration for the fact that it lasted so little and most important is the fact that we are still friends with Bruce Fairweather and Greg (Gilmore) that began in the group with us and when I listen to a song or I see a photo I think of the incredible person that Andy was and how it made me laugh, it was always a pleasure to work, laugh, talk about music, football and many other things with him.
It was a human being surprising and we are lacking.
The national group Las Robertas will open the show to Costa Rica.
It is true that you know his work, especially Eddie Vedder and for that you have chosen for the opening?
Yes, the production has sent us videos with various proposals and this was the group that we have the best, so we are keen to see what Las Robertas can offer online and it must be very distracting.
For what you always change the words of yello Ledbetter online?
It is a question for Ed (Eddie Vedder), so I do not know.
That's who sang and I believe it does with the first words he imagine.
As bassist, what are its influences?
There are so many...
Among the first I remember there is Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many influences, that I could talk all afternoon on the one that I love.
How Pearl Jam has managed to maintain the grunge despite the fact that it is no longer in fashion?
I believe that we all feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think, this reminds me of the groups that I have just mentioned, as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those who have all at once, and if this is relevant now, I think it is wonderful, because it is a music that is worth listening to and groups like Mudhoney are now the best music than ever.
At first, his music was a more obscure content and now it has become more positive.
What is this change?
It is interesting, because I believe that there are songs in the new album that appear to be lighter, but there are also songs, such as The End or Just Breathe qualified as very obscure songs, even if they can sound a little positive.
With the two, when Ed has played for me, I cried when I have listened to them and these are songs deeply obscure.
I think that if you are growing and there is a trauma in your life and you lose to a friend or relative, these things are beginning to influence your art and your music and songs, no doubt, this is for me.
I also think that can also be pleased and even as the music can be made.
