The Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gives the details of the air accident in which lost his life the Secretary of the Government, Francisco Blake and seven other people
The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) informed that the results highlighted on the accident in which lost his life the Secretary of Government, Francisco Blake Mora and seven other people, indicate that the helicopter has shocked directly against the soil in full structural integrity, without the pilot could try a forced landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Pérez Jácome, Secretary of Communications and Transport, said that before takeoff of the aircraft, the pilot found that the conditions of climate were adequate to fly.
"The elements that suggests that the unit was given to various contacts with the ground, the blades have had contact with the trees to 25 metres where the unit has lost the fuselage."
He also informed of the fact that the unit was designed for 19 people, therefore it met the requirements necessary to transport personnel.
In addition, he said that the investigations made in the area of impact do not report the emergence of parts on the ground.
