"This information supports the hypothesis of a functioning as normal at the time of the impact," he says.
During the press conference, the owner of the TBS, Jácome Pérez, has listed six important elements in the investigation.
Visual flight:
According to the normative aircraft, the flight was conducted according to the rules of the visual flight, which means that the crew must have visibility during the flight and on the ground.
Weather conditions:
The reports AICM mentioned in the appropriate conditions to take-off, and as the aircraft towards the border region between DF and the State of Mexico there were layers of low cloud cover.
Routes selected:
It is likely that "because of the conditions of cloud cover the crew has sought a height lower and more visibility to the valley of Cuernavaca.
Location of the impact.
The contact details of the impact and the last registration of the aircraft on radar coincide, probably before the impact there has not been or loss of control or alteration of the flight path.
Dispersal of the remains of the aircraft in an area reduced:
The information available so far suggests that the impact was held on a right trajectory and lateral.
The model of the remains of the aircraft suggests that the helicopter hit the ground in conditions of structural integrity.
It was not detected traces of fire or explosion:
In the area when there is still no trace in the remains of the aircraft of a type of explosion or fire.
The latest results from the investigation indicate that the aircraft had multiple contacts with the ground.
During the work of the field were found parts of the aircraft at a height of 9 mile 200 feet above sea level, the ground had a dégrées which ranges from seven to 30 degrees of incline.
The photographs show the sequence in which it was possibly thrown in along the route.
The information provides evidence that suggests that the helicopter may have had multiple impacts with the ground.
After careful research in an area more than the place, circled around the accident, it has not found the spread of the aircraft, which supports the presumption that the impact was held in conditions of structural integrity.
MSS announcement protocol to find the gene for obesity
Insurance Social is leading an investigation to discover the gene of obesity in children and young people; this is supported by experts in the NPI
The Mexican Social Insurance Institute (IMSS) announced that it is leading an investigation to discover the gene for obesity in the case of children and young people, known as "Genetics of obesity among children and adolescents" that will have the markers associated with being overweight.
In a news release, the head of the Investigation Unit Medical Biochemistry in Hospital of Medical Specialization Centre National du 20 e Siècle, Miguel Cruz López, explained that it had formed a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social.
This team is supported by specialists and students from third cycle of the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Centre of Investigation and for Advanced Study (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
The investigation to be invited to participate in the population with right, or not to run for units participating sports of IMSS to Valle de México, where the evidence to minors every Saturday from 8:00 hours.
He stressed that the protocol has started in the Sport Unit Cuauhtémoc (Estado de México Poniente) and that from 8 October, the business is carried out in the Sport Unit of Nezahualcóyolt (Estado de México Oriente).
After reaching the goal of having 500 or 600 minors, the study will continue in the Sport Unit Independencia (south of Distrito Federal) and finally in the Sport Unit Morelos (north of Distrito Federal).
He explained that the objective of this investigation and know the components and the importance of genetics in the development of obesity and identify among children and young Mexican of risk factors to prevent the onset of chronic degenerative diseases.
As we celebrate 14 November's World Diabetes Day, he indicated that the aim is to bring together three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years, with the consent and under the supervision of their parents, for the purposes of specific questionnaires relating to food.
They will also be asked about their physical activity and their family history of inheritance of their disease, to avoid the risk factors that trigger conditions like diabetes or kidney failure.
He detailed the Saturdays will apply to all participants anthropometric measurements (weight, height, waist circumference measurements), blood pressure, glucose levels, triglyceride, cholesterol and insulin and genetic (one sought to identify the people associated with childhood obesity).
Cruz López reported that this investigation is the result of the concern of health professionals for the alarming weight gain in the case of minors.
"The health surveys of 1999 and 2006 reported that in just six years there has been an increase, in the case of boys, from 77 percent in obesity and in the case of girls of 47 per cent; as regards the overweight also observed a dramatic increase," the specialist in the IMSS.
He indicated that the justification for the detection of markers is based in the fact that the country's population is different from other by its history.
He informed that, on average, the Mexican have a 65 percent of inheritance US-India, a 30 percent European and a five percent African and this is reflected in the people associated with diabetes and overweight.
He explained that, in general, the genetics of obesity is reflected in the inability of burning the excess energy that we consume (calories), which is in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for participants is the comprehensive evaluation of children, which can detect if there is a degree of overweight or obese.
Ila even said that the presence of folds (Acanthosis) on the neck and forearm indicate the likelihood of having metabolic alterations and even pré-diabètes.
The information is managed in a confidential manner, physicians provide in writing to parents, which the report explains each of the measures and changes in the way of life that they must do to prevent disease.
Cruz López explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic conditions: inactivity, which is the lack of physical activity daily, most of the day sitting in front of the TV and use of means of transport instead of going to foot on short distances.
Another issue is the high caloric intake, that is, the greater consumption of sugar-sweetened drinks, carbohydrates (tamales - block meat to corn flour wrapped in leaves -, bread, pizza, hamburgers, etc.) with a high content of fats and proteins and genetics analyzed in this Protocol.
The asphalt of the UNAM would avoid the blackcurrants
Rafael Herrera, researcher, Faculty of Chemistry of the UNAM, develops modified asphalts with polymers to produce a mixture with a better performance, regardless of environmental conditions and temperature
If the reported that the pavement were resolved, there would be no need to repair about 200 thousand blackcurrants each season of rain in the Metropolitan Area of Valle de México, warns Rafael Herrera, researcher in the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of the UNAM, which stated that if the process of construction and maintenance of the bituminous deck is adequate, blackcurrants could be reduced or even eliminated completely.
During its conference A opinion on technological, organised in the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, he announced that the laboratory for which it is responsible develops modified asphalts with polymers to produce a mixture with similar characteristics to those of the asphalt, but with mechanical resistance greater, both at high and low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera believed that this kind of modified asphalts could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, as some cities in the north of the country, to improve the performance and, therefore, the training of blackcurrants.
He explained that the asphalt, the more heavy oil, is a set of molecules of hydrocarbons, molecules with a molecular weight heavier, called, and asphaltenes molecules with a molecular weight, called malthènes, which together provide the paved his characteristic viscoelastic behaviour.
Viscoelastic behavior of asphalt is the fact that at temperatures, high of nearly 180 degrees, behaves as a liquid, 120 degrees C its viscosity is very large and 50 degrees C it presents a status almost solid, while at very low temperatures, the asphalt becomes brittle, he added.
This means that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform and changes during the day in terms of environmental conditions and temperature, warns the specialist chemical engineering.
The researcher to the FQ observed that the streets of Ciudad de México in their majority were covered by a flexible, composed of six layers of materials, including the last three imply the asphalt.
Between the uppermost layer is the layer of asphalt, formed by small stone house in asphalt and compacted later.
Each small stones that form the layer, signalât-il, is bathed year asphalt.
When the vehicle is registered in generating efforts, he allows that the forces are spread very well in the streets.
If we had of modified asphalt, they will spread better, opinât the chemical engineers.
On the layer of asphalt, he says, there is a last layer called layer of turnover, made in gemstone, i.e., sand, which is also bathed in asphalt.
As it is the layer in contact with the wheels of vehicles, she must have more mechanical force that the layer of asphalt and provide adhesion in the street.
As part of the pavement that receives and distributes the efforts, the layer of turnover also requires that it has an adequate thickness and the material from which it is made must be treated.
The climate, especially the humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially the water, "he says, because they affect significantly the performance of the layer of asphalt.
When the soil is getting wet, the water runs into the layer is so that it is difficult, which softened all layers of the pavement and therefore because of blackcurrants.
In the trial of a white, he says, which is the first strike is the film and only later is affected the layer of asphalt, but the injury was not immediately, but it is a process that must be treated to the first signals with maintenance programs.
The member of the National System Researchers explained that the burden of vehicles is another important factor for the training of blackcurrants and therefore the thickness of each layer of pavement must always be linked to the burden of vehicles and ensure its satisfaction, to avoid the frequent formation of blackcurrants.
Rafael Herrera warned that there is still much to investigate and work on the asphalt, for example, bituminous emulsions, which in other countries are already on the market, and to repair the blackcurrants easily and without having to use high temperatures.
