And was the work of the person of Cali which has identified the remains of Alfonso Cano
A dactyloscopiste of Cali made history as the man who confirmed the death of Alfonso Cano "."
The work of these officials is crucial.
The past 4 November a dactyloscopiste ITC Cali spent in history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Leader of terrorism: "Alfonso Cano" - testing its fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopistes who work in the local offices of the ITC, this week it was the turn of "availability of Eliazar González, a man of Puerto Tejada who has worked for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
Early in his career, González worked in the municipes of Chocó, where many times he had spent more than five days in the forest to arrive at the venue in which the bodies that were to be identified.
The year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after classes, he specialized in fingerprinting, which is the study of the skin friction, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano had been warned to Eliazar to take with him clothes at least for three days.
Something very important.
Friday night is party to Cauca in a helicopter Palmira.
He knew he had to identify two bodies and that the suspected one of them was that of the man who led the guérrilla oldest in the world, therefore he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigative team to the location of the body, it has not recognized by his physical appearance, because it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed as a peasant in the area, without glasses and much more.
But fingerprints do not lie.
Accompanied by a magnifying glass galtonienne, ink, a doctor and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye was deceived not: it was "Alfonso Cano."
This same night, the man originally from Puerto Tejada was the responsible person who confirmed to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzón that, yes, it was the Supreme Leader of terrorism.
In search of the footprint
For a dactyloscopiste to Sijín of Cali recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos has made to Eliazar González, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano," is very significant.
A lot of people is not our job.
Fingerprinting is an exact science, with no margin for error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
To identify the bodies, the dactyloscopistes support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of individuals captured.
When caught, many offenders have false identity cards or have not of documents.
We take their fingerprints and are in the database.
The researcher told that in a case of flight he had to remove a portion of wall of a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to get a safe full of jewellery and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable areas for a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to obtain the footprint of the hand and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
The fingerprints can also confirm or rule out suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently it was found a dead man, with bottles around him.
In the meantime the investigation it was determined that a parent can be suspect of crime and a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if this No. not guarantee that it is the murderer, this puts it on the crime scene.
A dactyloscopiste ITC explained that is extracted "the fingerprints of objects with reagents chemical or physical."
When they appear, using a doctor or a band for the levy.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the database of déclinquents, or the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there is still a lot of Colombian without papers," said the expert of the ITC.
He explained that all is not how it is shown in the television programme CSI.
As all that glitters is not gold, all that is is not necessarily a fingerprint.
However, it may be used, if the confrontation is necessary.
The "indignant" defy the authorities in New York
Hundreds of protesters pushing and shoving each other around the place Zuccotti for camping.
A large number of people accessing the evacuation order and has moved to a park.
The integrative movement occupies Wall Street have defied the authorities on Tuesday in New York in trying to re-enter, thanks to a judicial order, in place of Manhattan, where they were evacuated at dawn and when they tried to occupy another park of the Great Apple.
Hundreds of protesters pushing and shoving each other around the place Zuccotti, where they go through a judicial order that allows "indignant" camp again in this place, while the other part of the movement has responded to the evacuation in a park north of the city, where there have been new judgments.
"Our idea is that if the court does not allow us to camp in the place, we will install in another place and we will continue the legal fight to return to Zuccotti, and through sit-ins and peaceful demonstrations," dit-un spokespersons "Held Wall Street," Mark Bray.
Bray explained that the response of "indignant" in the evacuation of their camp personally dictated by the Mayor of New York, Michael Bloomberg, came to the courts, where the judge Lucy Billings issued an order prohibiting the forced evacuation of the area and allowed the demonstrators to remain in the camp.
In addition, the "indignant" occupied a new park at the confluence of the central Canal Street and Sixth Avenue, very close to the entrance to the tunnel Holland, between New York and New Jersey, the property of the Trinity Parish Church.
At least for a time they have been able to make the place, but after the Police had travelled there and arrested a few protesters, although Bray could not confirm the concrete figures, ensuring Efe the fact that he has seen a few journalists who had also spent handcuffs.
The organization ensures that there is for people who had installed in this place, where a delegation of religious leaders moved as a sign of support to the members of the movement and tried to intervene in favour of them before the Police.
Meanwhile, the place Zuccotti - which is a forum for private property - remains closed pending a celebration of a court hearing under this Tuesday, during which we must analyze the legality of the evacuation of this morning.
Some protesters moved so far and were distributed at that time copies of this judicial order and they were the same agents who were monitoring the place, which has caused some small clashes ,"" said Bray, who denounced the fact that some official hit the demonstrators.
The order prohibits judicial authorities to evacuate Held Wall Street or to apply laws published after the start of the occupation or prohibit the demonstrators to regain access to the park with tents or other properties that they used previously.
The Mayor Bloomberg told the press that, because of this judicial order, the city had suspended the reopening of the space to the public and the demonstrators, which it has alerted to the fact that local laws do not permit to settle with tents and sleeping bags.
The city councillor has defended the evacuation made personally to the place Zuccotti, an operation during which it has arrested 200 people and which was decided by the fact that the demonstrators "violated the law."
Bloomberg explained that he had given the order to evacuate the place because it was becoming "a place in which people were to protest, but to violate the laws and in some cases, to hurt other people," because "some stores had received threats" and residents were afraid "for their quality of life."
"The evacuation of this morning at dawn was repugnant and shows that Bloomberg is more concerned to defend the financial interests than those of American workers," added the spokesman of the movement, which accused the mayor of "do not respect freedom of expression."
Those responsible for the "Wall Street" Held also indicated that they felt they could not organise actions of "large" for Thursday in collaboration with community organizations and unions to commemorate two months of protestes, which began on 17 September.
